text: Patriarch Michael II may refer to: * Patriarch Michael II of Alexandria, Greek Patriarch of Alexandria in 870–903 * Michael II of Constantinople, Ecumenical Patriarch in 1143–1146 * Patriarch Michael II of Antioch, head of the Syriac Orthodox Church in 1292–1312 * Patriarch Michael II Fadel, ruled in 1793–1795
title: Patriarch Michael II
